[Black "French Tarrasch Introduction "]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6
{ The French Defense, regarded as one of Black's most solid defenses to 1.e4, while containing plenty of dynamic potential. }
2. d4 d5 3. Nd2
{ The Tarrasch Variation, around which this repertoire is constructed. This isn't quite as popular or critical as  3.Nc3  , but it has several benefits:   1. It avoids the 'Winawer Pin' ...♗b4   2. It allows White to support his d4 pawn with c2-c3.   3. It allows for a harmonious relocation of the Knights with ♘g1-e2-f4 and ♘b1-d2-f3.   4. It generally leads to more 'rational' positions than 3 ♘c3. }
