[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Course Introduction "]
[Black "Why a new course? "]
[Result "*"]

1. --
{ Fighting the French was my first ever Chessable course, and also the first opening course I ever published to this wide of an audience. While I was quite happy with the way it turned out at the time, roughly three and a half years later, there are a lot of things I now know I for sure could have done better. I have been updating the original course from time to time, but it just felt like the time was right for a complete overhaul. I had a different line vs. 3...Nf6 that I wanted to present, my lines against the ultra-critical 3...c5 4.exd5 Qxd5 didn't seem to be promising anymore, and my suggestion against the Rubinstein Variation - 3...dxe4 - had mostly been neutralized. Plus, a lot of publications have come out recently suggesting the French Defense for Black, and I'm hoping in this course to tackle them one by one. In essence, I'm building the initial course from the ground up. This isn't an update, it's essentially a completely new repertoire. Chessable's standards for publication were much different in 2017, and the original course did not feature many arrows or clickables as far as I can recall. This is another area in which I hope to substantially improve this version: I'm trying very hard to make it more user-friendly. Hopefully you understand my decision, and hopefully you enjoy the repertoire! }
*

