Nf6 21. Nd4 Nxd4 22. Qxd4
{ It seems to me like White has more or less stabilized his position. Black has a pawn for his exchange and definite compensation, but White is still material up, and Black needs to remain careful about potential attacks involving Rg1 and a battery on the long diagonal. }
