{ Black forgoes the usual ...c5 break for now. His alternative ambitions include breaking with ...e5, and, should White play e4-e5 at some point, breaking with ...f6. This is a line I've struggled against in blitz; Black often gets easy positions when White can't remember what he's meant to do. }
