O-O Nf6 9. Re1 cxd4
{ Temporarily going a pawn up, but White will regain it very quickly with Nb3xd4. There also aren't any particularly productive discovered checks at this exact moment. }
10. Nb3 Bb4 11. Bd2 Bxd2 12. Qxd2 O-O 13. Nfxd4
{ There's probably nothing wrong with taking with the other Knight, but this once keeps the option of Nc5 open. }
13... Bd7 14. Nc5
{ White has a nice position - active pieces, no clear active counterplay for Black yet. Bf3 and Rad1 are likely to follow. }
