{ Miedema does not cover this move. Outwardly, it's not terribly ambitious, but the plan is simply to play Be3 at some point, without allowing ...Ng4 in reply. }
12... Rfe8 13. c3 h6 14. Qd3
{ White prepares for a Rook to come to d1, while also hinting at an eventual Nf5. White should be ever so slightly for choice, although objectively it might well be closer to = than to +/=. }
