{ This is one attempt to swap Queens. Since we can win the pawn on e5, and also split Black’s pawns, we should probably go for it. }
18. Qxc6+ bxc6 19. Nxe5 c5 20. Nc4
{ White is better, as c5 is quite weak, and that pawn falling would give the first player quite a dangerous Queenside majority. }
