{ Don't play  7.Nb3  Qb4+  . } 7... Nc6
{ This is an inaccurate move order, as it allows White an extra option; a more pleasant way to re-gain the pawn. }
8. Ne4
{ This is one of the differences between Queen retreats. On d7 or d8, this wouldn't be a problem, meaning Black is free to delay the development of his g8 Knight if he so chooses. }
8... Qd8 9. Qe2 Be7 10. Rd1
{ As we saw in the previous chapter, if White can afford to re-gain the pawn leisurely with Qe2 and Rd1, he tends to be better off for doing so. }
