{ I was previously looking at  13.g3  . Chessable user solem14 pointed me towards the text, which looks like it might just be stronger. I think objectively Black should be equal in this line, but it does look like quite an interesting try practically. }
13... O-O 14. Bg5
{ 'Threatening' Bxf6, which should be especially dangerous with a Bishop on d3 pointing toward h7. }
14... Be7
{ This is the best move in the version with g3 in instead of h3. Here, White's position is just ever so slightly more harmonious with the more natural pawn advance having been played @@StartBracket@@as the g5 Bishop can retreat to h4 and then g3 if hit@@EndBracket@@. }
15. Qf3
{ White's plan is Rad1, possibly followed by expansion on the Queenside with c2-c4. }
