{ This is Black's other main possibility. It's a bit more ambitious, but also somewhat looser. White's b3 and Bb2 plan can perhaps be met by ...Rh6, activating the Rook in an original way. }
17. Qd4 Bd6 18. Bc4 Bd7
{ This is Black's main try; developing a piece, but I think White still has a bit of pressure. }
19. Bd2
{ Intending Bc3. You can make your case about what you think about this position, but I think White is slightly for preference, given his more 'normal' looking position, but Black certainly has his ideas. It's a complicated position for sure, and Black seems to lack the ability to immediately 'kill the game' like in the 16...h6 variation. }
