Re1
{ Black's managed to create a battery, and now has the opportunity to stick a piece on d3. }
12... Nd3
{ Now White is forced to give up his Light Squared Bishop for a Knight. However, obtaining this has cost the second player a lot of time. }
13. Bxd3 Bxd3 14. Nc3
{ The Bishop on d3, despite being outside the pawn chain, will have a tough time finding a good square, while again, Black has lost a lot of time with...♕b6-a6, ...♘c6-b4 and...♗d7-b5-d3. Also, White's proud centre remains very much intact, cramping Black's pieces not to mention he has already spent his...c5 break, and...f6 just seems weakening at this point. The game Mons-Buhmann, Germany 2014 continued... }
14... Bb4 15. Bd2 Bxc3 16. Bxc3 Ne7 17. Bb4
{ White has an excellent Opposite Coloured Bishop position. } *

