1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 Bd7
{ This move is tried from time to time, but it doesn't have much independent significance. }
4. Ngf3
{ It's possible to play other moves, but this is the simplest, as Black hardly has anything better than transposing back into a line we've seen elsewhere. }
4... dxe4
{ Okay, Black has tried other moves in practice, but no other move really makes sense to me, as this seems to be the only move that justifies the Bishop's placement on d7. }
5. Nxe4 { We've reached the Fort Knox Variation from the 3... dxe4 chapter. } *

